The fiancee of a man on trial for murdering a black teenager in cold blood has told how they went back to their hotel, ordered a pizza and drank rum and Cokes straight after the killing.

Michael Dunn, 47, is accused of murdering Jordan Davis, a 17-year-old, after he refused to turn down loud rap music he and his friends were playing in his car parked outside a store in Jacksonville, Florida.

Rhonda Rouer, who was inside the store when the shooting happened, said she heard shots and was immediately told to get in the car by Dunn, who drove them back to their hotel.

